Dear 33, 

 You were one for the books. You taught me a lot. You broke me down to understand & grow. You opened my eyes to genuine humans, letting go of pride & ego, and showed me humility. You taught me I cannot, nor do I want to handle things alone. You taught me how to fully live. Going into my 34th year of this existence I know exactly what I want in my life. Exactly who I want to surround myself with, and the kind of human I want to be in others lives. Growing & learning from my mistakes is not only making me a better person, but a softer human. I am choosing peace this year. Choosing health, happiness, and abundance. I can’t wait to see what this year has in store. Thank you to all of my friends & my family who have been by my side through every minute of this wild life. The good & not so easy times. You are my pack, and I am so grateful. Also, never lose your inner child. Your inner child is so much fun. Love you all. 

34, Let’s rock n roll baby.
